<task id="task-9068" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Cancel Visual Testing subscriptions</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can cancel your Visual Testing Professional (VTP) subscription by following these steps:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Sign in to <xref href="https://testops.katalon.io/login" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Katalon TestOps</xref>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the desired Account.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol> icon, then select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Subscription Management</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Additional Subscription</uicontrol> section, locate your <ph conkeyref="name-variables/visual-testing" class="- topic/ph "/> subscription and click <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">option</i> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Cancel</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult "><image width="700" href="../upgrade_subscriptions/Additional_subscription_-_upgrade_visual_testing.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Additional subscription - Cancel Visual Testing</alt></image></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the cancellation dialog, click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Cancel</uicontrol> to confirm.</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">You have canceled the next billing of your VTP subscription. You can still use the current subscription until its expiry date. After that, you can no longer use VTP unless you re-subscribe. </result></taskbody></task>